<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05028f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05028f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05028f"> 28(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> magic food</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; to Justin Martyr the flesh and blood of Christ were the <mark>soul&apos;s food</mark>, and became its very life by assimilation; Iren&aelig;us saw in the bread after its consecration a supernatural element as well as a natural, the supernatural element being the mysterious presence of the crucified Christ in both bread and wine; <small> J.T. Lloyd, <a name="GODE" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#GODE"><cite title="source">God-Eating</cite></a>, (1921) 19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
